{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idec0e151c-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s70505"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"70505"},"text":"§ 70505.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Lunar outpost","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idec0e151d-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s70505/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Establishment","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"As the Administration works toward the establishment of a lunar outpost, the Administration shall make no plans that would require a lunar outpost to be occupied to maintain its viability. Any such outpost shall be operable as a human-tended facility capable of remote or autonomous operation for extended periods.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idec0e151e-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53","identifier":"/us/usc/t51/s70505/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Designation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The United States portion of the first human-tended outpost established on the surface of the Moon shall be designated the “Neil A. Armstrong Lunar Outpost”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idec0e151f-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3431"},"tex